==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Geosynclinal
<hw>Ge`o*syn*cli"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ge`a</grk>, <grk>gh^</grk>, the earth + E.
<ets>synclinal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>the downward bend
or subsidence of the earth's crust, which allows of the gradual
accumulation of sediment, and hence forms the first step in the making
of a mountain range; -- opposed to <xex>geanticlinal</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Geothermometer</ent>⟦br⟧
